HEADWORD: Diseaseful
<hw>Dis*ease"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Causing uneasiness.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Disgraceful to the king and <qex>diseaseful</qex> to the
people.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abounding with disease; producing diseases; <as>as,
a <ex>diseaseful</ex> climate</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diseasefulness</ent>⟦br⟧
